txt.en: 'The hobbits have welcomed me with open arms and full mugs....'
'I'm not over charging you, if you think you can get a better price then try; or better yet dig the ore out of the ground yourself!'
'Fine, fine! I will do as you insist...but I do not like it.'
'If that were my will; it would be quicker and cleaner than your way but I choose to do other things. It's not your price that I find irritating.'
'It is the fact that you are charging me so much because I am an Elf.'
'And if I am? It's my ore, it's my choice and it's my final price!'
'Hey! The two of you ought to quite down or part ways or I'll give you a taste of my mace.'
